The paper is primarily focused on few-shot object segmentation using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of standard backbone networks and the comparison of results with pre-trained models, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of pixelwise annotation and ground-truth segmentation, which are common techniques in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
